# Codomyrmex ↔ Cursor (committed pointers)

Use this file alongside `cursorrules/general.cursorrules` and `.cursor/rules/*.mdc` (native Cursor project rules). It does not replace module-specific rules.

## Repo contract

- Read root `CLAUDE.md` for build commands (`uv sync`, `uv run pytest`) and architecture summary.
- Read root `AGENTS.md` for surface navigation and module index.
- Read root `SPEC.md` for functional scope when behavior is ambiguous.
- Prefer `uv run` for all Python tooling; dependencies live in `pyproject.toml`.

## MCP tools relevant in Cursor

When the Codomyrmex MCP server is attached:

- `codomyrmex.ide_cursor_workspace_info` — workspace + `.cursorrules` presence
- `codomyrmex.ide_cursor_get_active_file` — mtime-based active file hint
- `codomyrmex.ide_cursor_rules_read` — bounded read of `.cursorrules`

If the server cwd is not the repo root, set environment variable `CODOMYRMEX_CURSOR_WORKSPACE` to the repository path.

## Implementation reference

- `src/codomyrmex/ide/cursor/` — `CursorClient`
- `src/codomyrmex/ide/mcp_tools.py` — MCP entrypoints
- `docs/development/cursor-integration.md` — full wiring notes
